##-----HTTP

HTTP              Request                          Response

1. Start Line     version: http/1.1                 version: http1.1
                  Methods: GET,POST,PUT,DELETE     Equal and status code.
                  /search?.q=something
                  
2. Headers        Host: www.google.com             cookie: .....
                  Token: ......                    cookie: .....
                  
3. Blank Line
4. Body           in a email: Username, password   HTML web page.

# An API done over the internet is called Web Service.

	1.##-----HTTP Start Line
	REQUEST
	Method(space)+API Program Folder Location+Parameters(space)HTTP Version

	RESPONSE
	HTTP Version+Status Code

	METHODS:
  GET Is Idempotent
  POST Is not Idempotent
  PUT Is Idempotent
  DELETE Is Idempotent
  
	2.##-----TTP HEADERS

	2.1. Standard Request Fields
	A-IM
	Accept-Language
	Accept-Datatime
	Authorization
	Cache-Control
	Content-Type
	Date
	...

	2.2 Standard Response Fields
	Allow
	Cache-Control
	Expires
	Server
	Set-Cookie

  3.##-----Blank Line
	
	4.##-----BODY
	Content sent to/from the API
	
	What header line describes type of content in the HTTP Body?
	Content-Type: (Data, image, web, audio, video)
	
	What content types can be used for sending/receiving data?
	XML, JSON
	
	
	
	

	
